e early evolutionary history of the family Aporrhaidae. Pal\u00e4ontologische Zeitschrift, 83(4), 533.</ref>\n|\n*''Toarctocera subpunctata''\n|\n* All the Formation\n|\nThousands of Specimens.\n|\nA [[Aporrhaidae]] sea [[Snail]]. Among the latest described from the formation, is  one of the earliest certain aporrhaidae. Characterised by large spines growing at the head of the cunch.\n|\n|-\n|\n[[Cryptaulax (gastropod)|Cryptaulax]]<ref name=\"M\u00fcnsterClamA\"/><ref name=\"M\u00fcnsterClamB\"/><ref name=\"CaswellClamA\"/><ref name=\"RoemerClamA\"/><ref name=\"AgassizClamA\"/>\n|\n*''Cryptaulax armatum''\n|\n* All the Formation\n|\nThousands of Specimens.\n|\nA [[Cryptaulacidae]] sea [[Snail]].\n|\n|-\n|\n[[Neritaria]]<ref name=\"M\u00fcnsterClamA\"/><ref name=\"M\u00fcnsterClamB\"/><ref name=\"CaswellClamA\"/><ref name=\"RoemerClamA\"/><ref name=\"AgassizClamA\"/>\n|\n*''Neritaria papilio''\n|\n* All the Formation\n|\nThousands of Specimens.\n|\nA [[Neritariidae]] sea [[Snail]].\n|\n[[File:Museo delle Grigne - EL50B - Neritaria otomorpha.jpg|thumb|center|195px|Single specimen]]\n|-\n|\n[[Zygopleura]]<ref name=\"M\u00fcnsterClamA\"/><ref name=\"M\u00fcnsterClamB\"/><ref name=\"CaswellClamA\"/><ref name=\"RoemerClamA\"/><ref name=\"AgassizClamA\"/>\n|\n*''Zygopleura septemcincta''\n|\n* All the Formation\n|\nThousands of Specimens.\n|\nA [[Zygopleuridae]] sea [[Snail]].\n|\n[[File:Zygopleura corvaliana.jpg|thumb|center|195px|Specimens]]\n|-\n|\n[[Trochus]]<ref name=\"M\u00fcnsterClamA\"/><ref name=\"M\u00fcnsterClamB\"/><ref name=\"CaswellClamA\"/><ref name=\"RoemerClamA\"/><ref name=\"AgassizClamA\"/>\n|\n*''Trochus subduplicatus''\n|\n* All the Formation\n|\nThousands of Specimens.\n|\nA [[Trochidae]] sea [[Snail]].\n|\n[[File:Kreiselschnecke Trochus subduplicatus.jpg|thumb|center|195px|Specimens]]\n|-\n|}\n\n====Cephalopoda====\n{| class = \"wikitable\"\n|-\n! Genus\n! Species\n! Stratigraphic position\n! Material\n! Notes\n! Images\n|-\n|\n[[Nautilidae]]<ref nam